    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-26T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="418"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Great Britain/292: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_MAW1" type="to"
                            >Mellon</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-26T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 26, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. Department’s circular February 26th, 11 A.M. Treasury draft of agreement to
                    carry out Congressional Resolution regarding debt postponement has been handed
                    to British Ambassador<note n="52" xml:id="d418fn52">
                        <persName corresp="#p_LSRC1">Sir Ronald Lindsay</persName>.</note> today.
                    Treasury anxious to expedite action. Department does not desire that you make
                    special call on officials regarding this but in connection with other matters
                    hopes you will find opportunity to inquire whether prompt action can be
                    expected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
